{{Infobox astronomical survey}}
The '''Las Campanas [[Redshift survey|Redshift Survey]]''' is considered the first attempt to map a large area of the universe out to a [[redshift]] of ''z'' = 0.2. It was begun in 1991 using the [[Las Campanas Observatory|Las Campanas telescope]] in [[Chile]] to catalog 26418 separate galaxies.<ref name="utoronto">{{cite web|url=http://qold.astro.utoronto.ca/~lin/lcrs.html|publisher=qold.astro.utoronto.ca|title=The Las Campanas Redshift Survey|accessdate=2016-12-26|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120630215300/http://qold.astro.utoronto.ca/~lin/lcrs.html|archivedate=2012-06-30|df=}}</ref> It is considered one of the first surveys to document the so-called "[[end of greatness]]" where the [[Cosmological Principle]] of isotropy could be seen. [[Supercluster]]s<ref>{{cite journal |author=[[Sergei F. Shandarin|Shandarin, Sergei F.]];[[Capp Yess|Yess, Capp]]|title=Detection of Network Structure in the Las Campanas Redshift Survey|journal=The Astrophysical Journal|date=1998|volume= 505|issue= 1|pages=12–17|arxiv=astro-ph/9705155|doi=10.1086/306135|bibcode=1998ApJ...505...12S}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=[[Somnath Bharadwaj|Bharadwaj, S.]];[[A. K. Gupta|Gupta, A. K.]]; [[T. R. Seshadri|Seshadri, T. R.]]|title=Nature of clustering in the Las Campanas redshift survey|journal=[[Astronomy and Astrophysics]]|date=1999|volume=351|pages=405–412|arxiv=astro-ph/9903252 | bibcode=1999A&A...351..405B}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Einasto, J.|author2=Einasto, M.|author3=Hütsi, G.|author4=Saar, E.|author5=Tucker, D. L.|author6=Tago, E.|author7=Müller, V.|author8=Heinämäki, P.|author9=Allam, S. S.|title=Clusters and Superclusters in the Las Campanas Redshift Survey|journal=Astronomy and Astrophysics|date=2003|volume=410 |issue=2|pages=425–443|bibcode=2003A&A...410..425E |doi=10.1051/0004-6361:20031105|arxiv = astro-ph/0304546 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=[[Somnath Bharadwaj|Bharadwaj, S.]], [[Varun Sahni|Sahni, V.]], [[B.S. Sathyaprakash|Sathyaprakash, B.S.]], [[Sergei F. Shandarin|Shandarin, Sergei F.]], [[Capp Yess|Yess, Capp]]|title=Evidence for Filamentarity in the Las Campanas Redshift Survey|journal=The Astrophysical Journal|date=2000|volume=528 |issue=1|pages=21–29|bibcode=2000ApJ...528...21B |doi=10.1086/308163|arxiv = astro-ph/9904406 }}</ref> and [[Void (astronomy)|voids]] are prominent features in the survey.

